==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Watt
<hw>Watt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the distinguished
mechanician and scientist, <person>James
<etsep>Watt</etsep></person>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A unit of
power or activity equal to 10<exp>7</exp> C.G.S. units of power, or to
work done at the rate of one joule a second. An English horse power is
approximately equal to 746 watts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

